Introduction

Yellow Bee was a five-member girl group under A.D. Entertainment (formerly known as Addiction Entertainment). They debuted on September 23, 2017, with the single "Hiccup."

On July 31, 2020, their agency released an official statement announcing their disbandment, citing "promiscuous behavior" in one member’s private life. However, this was later clarified by Ari, who revealed that the situation stemmed from sexual harassment by the managers and agency staff. Their disbandment was officially confirmed on July 12, 2020.
